HEADWORD: Ooecium
<hw>O*oe"ci*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Ooecia</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<grk>w,'o`n</grk> an egg + <?/ a house.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>One of the special zooids, or cells, of Bryozoa, destined to
receive and develop ova; an ovicell. See <er>Bryozoa</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
